        "The Lord's Prayer restructures human priority: God's name (hallowed), God's kingdom (come), God's will (done) — all before the first personal request for daily bread. Kingdom citizens pray outward before praying inward. This order is itself a spiritual discipline.",
        "The entire Sermon describes a new kind of community — characterised by radical generosity, internal integrity, love of enemies, freedom from anxiety, and a single-minded focus on God's kingdom. This is not aspirational self-help. It is the natural fruit of lives transformed by the Spirit Jesus would send."
